public interface IBuildDefinition
extends IBuildDefinitionHandle, IAuditable, IBuildItem

The build definition is a primary identifier for a set of builds. A definition is composed of one or more configuration elements that make up the configurable data in the definition. Example configuration elements provided by com.ibm.team.build are General, Ant, Schedule, Expected Contributions, and Properties. In addition, new configuration elements can be contributed via the com.ibm.team.build.common.buildConfigurationElements extension point.

Since:
0.5
